  Average turnaround    : 6.00
  Average response time : 3.50
  Deadline misses       : 0 / 4


========================================================
Round Robin
========================================================
Preemptive. Each ready process gets at most quantum=3 time units per turn. Arrivals at a time-slice boundary are queued before the preempted process.

Execution timeline:
  [ 0,  3)  P1
  [ 3,  6)  P2
  [ 6,  8)  P3
  [ 8,  9)  P4
  [ 9, 10)  P1

Compact Gantt view:
  |0 P1 |3 P2 |6 P3 |8 P4 |9 P1 |10

Per-process results:
Process        Arr   Burst    Prio  Deadline  FirstStart    Finish   Waiting  Turnaround  Response   Missed
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
P1               0       4       2        30           0        10         6          10         0       no
P2               1       3       1        30           3         6         2           5         2       no
P3               2       2       1        30           6         8         4           6         4       no
P4               3       1       1        30           8         9         5           6         5       no

Summary metrics:
  Makespan              : 10
  Total busy time       : 10
  CPU utilization       : 100.00%
  Throughput            : 0.40 processes/unit-time
  Average waiting time  : 4.25
  Average turnaround    : 6.75
  Average response time : 2.75
  Deadline misses       : 0 / 4


==================== POLICY COMPARISON ====================
Policy                              Avg Wait  Avg Turnaround      Avg Resp    Misses      Util %
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
FCFS - First Come First Served          3.50            6.00          3.50         0      100.00
SJF - Shortest Job First                2.50            5.00          2.50         0      100.00
Priority Scheduling                     3.50            6.00          3.50         0      100.00
Round Robin                             4.25            6.75          2.75         0      100.00

Interpretation hints:
  - Lower waiting/turnaround time is usually better for batch-style workloads.
  - Lower response time is important for interactive workloads.
  - Round Robin often improves response time, but can increase turnaround time.
  - Deadline misses show whether a policy is suitable for time-bound workloads.
